# DigitalOcean redeploy

When you finish changes that affect the **deployed** app (root `src/`, `scanner-app/`, `wire-scanner-app/`, shared `lib/`, or DigitalOcean spec/scripts):

1. Commit and **`git push origin main`** (or the branch in `deployments/digitalocean/.env.deploy` as `DO_GITHUB_BRANCH`).
2. **Always trigger DigitalOcean** from the **repo root** using one of:
   - **`npm run deploy:do`** (runs `deployments/digitalocean/deploy.ps1`), or  
   - **`powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File deployments/digitalocean/deploy.ps1`**

   This updates the App Platform spec if needed and runs `doctl apps create-deployment --force-rebuild`. Requires `deployments/digitalocean/.env.deploy` with `DO_ACCESS_TOKEN` on the machine that runs it.

   Do **not** rely on “push only” unless the user has confirmed GitHub Actions secrets (`DIGITALOCEAN_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `DIGITALOCEAN_APP_ID`) are set — see `deployments/digitalocean/DEPLOY_SIMPLE.md` §4.

Do this **at the end of the same session** after such changes unless the user explicitly opts out. If push or deploy fails, say what failed and fix or retry.
